Jul 13 2008 	Springhill Suites / Great location great for families	Went to a couple Cubs games last week with my son and decided to stay downtown. Booked the SpringHIll Suites and was very very pleased. I'll make this quick and to the point:Positives: Location is AWESOME. It's right by everything. The redline on Grand, tons of great places to eat, excellent shopping...it's easy to get to if you're driving, and again, in terms of location, it can't be beat.We got a great price. Basically 250 bucks got me the room, taxes and various chargees, a free buffet breakfast and parking. (in fact $41 of the $250 was parking related.)Staff was friendly and professional. We had requested early checkin and was actually able to get in our room by 11:00Room was nice. Was it the nicest room I've ever been in? Nope. But it was spacious, clean and was a perfect spot for my son and I. If you are looking for 4 star luxury, this isn't it, but if youi are looking for nice, new, clean, well located, family friendly, this place is perfect. Negatives: I don't really have any complaints about this place at all. $41 seemed a little steep for parking, but it is downtown, and we did get unlimited in / out privledges, so I'm not really complaining about the hotel itself, moreso I'm just kinda bummed that I have to pay that much to park in the first place.Bottom line...I do recommend this hotel. It was a great buy, great location, and nice room. And by the way, the breakfast wasn't bad either. I'll be back.	
