Jul 1 2008 	Great Value Family Friendly	The Springhill Suites in downtown Chicago was a great selection for my young family. We came to Chicago to visit the museums and downtown area. The room was spacious and very clean. The staff was friendly, gave good advice about the museums, and quite accommodating. The morning breakfast had a good selection of pastries, breads, fruits, juices, and hot items as well. Valet parking was expensive (not surprising for the location) but the staff was helpful and we had no problems. The only downside was the location was a bit far to walk to the museums. If you are interested in visiting the theater district or shops along Michigan Ave., this is a great location. But the walk to the aqaurium and planetarium was at least 2 1/2 miles (felt longer with the kids). We decided to take the el on the second day which helped a bit.We would definitely choose this hotel again, but just plan differently about how to get around.	
